The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) through its task force is monitoring the Ekiti 2022 governorship elections. Operatives of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) were also sighted at some polling units in Ado-Ekiti.   Ekiti poll: EFCC arrests PDP agent for alleged vote buying     Security operatives snatch money at Ekiti poling unit     Meet Ekiti polling unit with 15 registered voters   Although they declined to speak with our correspondent, it was gathered that the EFCC task force team was on ground to monitor activities of vote buying. The officials adorned in their jackets are going around various units.